Balanced Budget and Ministerial Accountability Act
Minister of State for Local Governments and Rural Communities
Expected Results for the 2024-2025 Fiscal Year Regulation
Application of this regulation
1  This regulation applies to the Minister of State for Local Governments and Rural Communities for the 2024/2025 fiscal year.

Definition
2  In this regulation, "Act" means the Balanced Budget and Ministerial Accountability Act.

Minister of State for Local Governments and Rural Communities
3  The expected results that the Minister of State for Local Governments and Rural Communities is to achieve for the purposes of section 5 (3) of the Act are as follows:

(a)work closely with the Union of British Columbia Municipalities as it prepares for executive committee engagements, quarterly meetings, advocacy days and its annual convention;

(b)hold meetings with representatives of rural and remote communities, regional districts, municipalities and First Nations, in order to understand their opportunities, needs and challenges;

(c)submit a report to Cabinet on the results referred to in paragraphs (a) and (b) on or before March 31, 2025.

[Provisions relevant to the enactment of this regulation: Balanced Budget and Ministerial Accountability Act, S.B.C. 2001, c. 28, s. 9.]

